Subject: rPSA-2007-0181-1 gnome-ssh-askpass openssh openssh-client
 openssh-server

rPath Security Advisory: 2007-0181-1
Published: 2007-09-10
Products: rPath Linux 1
Rating: Minor
Exposure Level Classification:
    Local System User Deterministic Weakness
Updated Versions:
    gnome-ssh-askpass=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1-devel/4.7p1-0.1-1
    openssh=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1-devel/4.7p1-0.1-1
    openssh-client=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1-devel/4.7p1-0.1-1
    openssh-server=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1-devel/4.7p1-0.1-1

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2007-4752
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-1706
    http://www.openssh.com/txt/release-4.7

Description:
    Previous versions of openssh could use a trusted X11 cookie if creation
    of an untrusted cookie failed.

